org.apache.flex.compiler.definitions

Interface IConstantDefinition

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IDefinition, IDocumentableDefinition, IVariableDefinition
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ConstantDefinition

    public interface IConstantDefinition
extends IVariableDefinition
    A definition representing a const declaration.

    An IConstantDefinitionIVariableNode for which isConst() is true.

    For example, the declaration 

    public const N:int = 1;
    creates a constant definition whose base name is "N", whose namespace reference is to the public namespace, and whose type reference is named "int".

    A constant definition is contained within a file scope, a package scope, a class scope, an interface scope, or a function scope; it does not contain a scope.
